IN FUN CONDITION ♪

00:39.706 --> 00:41.499
{\an8}♪ PREPARE
TO COUNT DOWN ♪

00:41.583 --> 00:44.169
{\an8}♪<i> ROCKET POWER</i> ♪

00:44.252 --> 00:46.713
{\an8}[seagulls screeching]

00:56.347 --> 00:57.474
{\an8}- YEAH!

00:57.557 --> 00:59.058
{\an8}- OH!

00:59.142 --> 01:00.727
{\an8}[all shouting]

01:00.810 --> 01:02.520
{\an8}- AGH!
OOF!

01:02.604 --> 01:03.897
{\an8}- [shrieks]

01:03.980 --> 01:04.772
{\an8}OH!

01:04.855 --> 01:06.107
- COME ON!
LET'S GO!

01:06.191 --> 01:07.150
HURRY UP!

01:07.233 --> 01:10.487
[wheel squeaking and rattling]

01:10.570 --> 01:12.071
ALL RIGHT!

01:20.580 --> 01:21.790
[tires screech]

01:21.873 --> 01:24.375
- WHOA!
WHOA!

01:24.459 --> 01:26.377
WHOA-OH-OH-OH!

01:26.461 --> 01:27.587
[shouts]

01:28.880 --> 01:29.839
OW!

01:29.923 --> 01:30.840
NO WONDER THEY CALL IT
SCAB MOUNTAIN.

01:30.924 --> 01:33.009
- WHAT DID I TELL YOU?

01:33.092 --> 01:35.512
- I WAS HOPING
THAT WAS JUST A RUMOR.

01:35.595 --> 01:36.638
DOES IT HURT?

01:36.721 --> 01:38.389
- YES!
DUH!

01:38.473 --> 01:39.182
- THIS IS SO MUCH FUN!

01:39.265 --> 01:41.184
- WHAT ARE WE WAITING FOR?

01:41.267 --> 01:42.310
OTTO SAYS, "LET'S ROCK!"

01:42.393 --> 01:45.355
- COME ON!
LET'S BOMB THE HILL AGAIN!

01:45.438 --> 01:46.856
- LAST ONE TO THE TOP
IS A LAME-O!

01:46.940 --> 01:48.358
- WELL, THAT'S FUNNY...

01:48.441 --> 01:51.736
'CAUSE I'M LOOKING AT
A WHOLE BUNCH OF LAME-Os!

01:51.820 --> 01:53.488
- WHAT'S THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

01:53.571 --> 01:55.698
I DON'T SEE YOU
TEARING UP THE MOUNTAIN.

01:55.782 --> 01:58.827
- THAT'S BECAUSE I DON'T BOARD
ON THE BUNNY SLOPE.

01:58.910 --> 02:01.496
- BUNNY SLOPE?
YEAH, RIGHT.

02:01.579 --> 02:04.541
- THIS DORKY LITTLE MUD HILL
IS NOTHING

02:04.624 --> 02:07.085
COMPARED
TO BRUISED MAN'S CURVE.

02:07.168 --> 02:09.711
BUT, HEY, I GUESS
I'LL HAVE TO TELL

02:09.795 --> 02:11.714
EVERY LIVING SOUL
IN OCEAN SHORES

02:11.798 --> 02:13.758
THAT OTTO ROCKET
IS A SCAREDY-CAT.

02:13.842 --> 02:16.052
- SCAREDY-CAT?

02:16.135 --> 02:17.637
I'M NOT SCARED OF ANYTHING,

02:17.720 --> 02:20.223
ESPECIALLY
ANY MOUNTAIN BOARD COURSE.

02:20.306 --> 02:21.891
- YOU'RE ON, LITTLE DWEEB.

02:21.975 --> 02:23.810
BUT BE PREPARED.

02:23.893 --> 02:27.438
NOBODY BUT NOBODY MAKES IT DOWN
BRUISED MAN'S CURVE

02:27.522 --> 02:29.983
WITHOUT LEAVING
A PIECE OF THEMSELVES BEHIND.

02:30.066 --> 02:31.109
- OH, NO!

02:31.192 --> 02:33.444
BAD IMAGE!
BAD IMAGE!

02:33.528 --> 02:34.988
- SO WHAT ARE WE WAITING FOR?

02:35.071 --> 02:36.573
LET'S GO CHECK IT OUT,
LARS.

02:36.656 --> 02:39.659
- [laughs]

02:39.742 --> 02:41.661
[gong resounds]

02:41.744 --> 02:45.540
[all panting]

02:47.417 --> 02:48.543
- [screaming]

02:48.626 --> 02:49.586
- [wailing]

02:49.669 --> 02:52.380
- WHOA...

02:52.463 --> 02:56.426
- [shrieking]

02:56.509 --> 02:59.679
- [laughs]

02:59.762 --> 03:00.930
WHAT DID I TELL YOU?

03:01.014 --> 03:03.808
- [scoffs]
IT'S NOTHING.

03:03.892 --> 03:04.934
I CAN DO IT.

03:05.018 --> 03:08.021
- PAGING EVERY BROKEN BONE
IN YOUR BODY...

03:08.104 --> 03:09.188
- CHILL, REG.

03:09.272 --> 03:09.939
YOU'RE EMBARRASSING ME.

03:10.023 --> 03:12.567
LOOK, A FEW PRACTICE RUNS,

03:12.650 --> 03:13.610
AND I'LL FIGURE THIS COURSE OUT.

03:13.693 --> 03:16.154
NO PROBLEMO!

03:16.237 --> 03:17.989
I AM, AFTER ALL, ME.

03:18.072 --> 03:21.075
YO, LARS, I'LL RACE YOU,

03:21.159 --> 03:23.912
BUT I NEED, LIKE, A DAY OR SO
TO GET READY.

03:23.995 --> 03:26.831
HOW'S FRIDAY MORNING,
9:00 A.M. SHARP?

03:26.915 --> 03:27.999
- [laughs]

03:28.082 --> 03:29.125
THIS IS SO SWEET.

03:29.208 --> 03:31.127
I GET THE DORK
TO WHOMP HIMSELF!

03:31.210 --> 03:33.212
[laughs]

03:41.262 --> 03:43.306
- [panting and groaning]

03:43.389 --> 03:45.642
- THERE'S THE LITTLE
DIRTY ROCKET CUZ,

03:45.725 --> 03:46.684
BACK FROM A BIG DAY
OF WIPEOUTS.

03:46.768 --> 03:48.853
[laughs]

03:48.937 --> 03:51.648
HEY, YOU GOT A BRUISE
THE SHAPE OF MAUI...

03:51.731 --> 03:54.150
AND OAHU AND KAUAI.

03:54.233 --> 03:57.320
- YOU SHOULD SEE
WHERE THE BIG ISLAND IS.

03:57.403 --> 03:58.571
OW...

04:02.367 --> 04:04.035
WHAT ARE YOU GUYS
LOOKING AT?

04:04.118 --> 04:06.579
- YOU'RE A MESS, DUDE.

04:06.663 --> 04:08.581
- THANKS, BRO.

04:08.665 --> 04:09.916
- YOU ALL RIGHT?

04:09.999 --> 04:12.001
- [angrily]
I'M GREAT.

04:12.085 --> 04:13.002
OW...

04:13.086 --> 04:14.837
- ON A SCALE OF 1 TO 10...

04:14.921 --> 04:15.630
- 12.

04:15.713 --> 04:17.089
- OOH...

04:17.173 --> 04:20.802
- OTTO, I'VE BEEN THINKING.

04:20.885 --> 04:23.388
I DON'T THINK YOU CAN GO DOWN
BY YOURSELF.

04:23.471 --> 04:26.307
- I'M NOT GOING WITH HIM!
COUNT ME OUT!

04:26.391 --> 04:27.892
- CHILL, SAMMY.
[scoffs]

04:27.976 --> 04:29.185
I'M ALL FOR CREAMIN' LARS,

04:29.269 --> 04:30.687
BUT I THINK
WE SHOULD FIGURE OUT A PLAN

04:30.770 --> 04:32.647
HOW TO HELP YOU NAIL
THAT RUN.

04:34.983 --> 04:36.484
- I DON'T NEED ANY HELP.

04:37.610 --> 04:38.736
OOF!

04:38.820 --> 04:40.863
OW!

04:40.947 --> 04:42.573
- YES, YOU DO.

04:43.116 --> 04:45.410
[hawk screeches]

04:51.791 --> 04:55.044
- WHOA...

04:55.128 --> 04:57.213
[rocks crumbling]

05:02.093 --> 05:03.469
OH!

05:06.389 --> 05:08.016
[keys clacking]

05:10.935 --> 05:12.478
WHOA!
OOF!

05:21.738 --> 05:23.322
OH!

05:27.243 --> 05:29.203
- OKAY, TWIST, CUT!

05:29.287 --> 05:30.413
[camera whirs]

05:30.496 --> 05:32.248
- THIS IS SO GNARLY!

05:32.331 --> 05:33.416
[computer beeping]

05:33.499 --> 05:36.294
ANYBODY WHO TRIED
BRUISED MAN'S CURVE

05:36.377 --> 05:37.003
IS CRAZY.

05:37.086 --> 05:40.423
BESIDES YOU, I MEAN.

05:40.506 --> 05:41.215
- HEY, NOT TO WORRY.

05:41.299 --> 05:43.593
I RAN ALL THE NUMBERS AGAIN.

05:43.676 --> 05:44.927
WE CAN MAKE THIS HAPPEN.

05:45.011 --> 05:48.056
[computer beeping]

05:49.807 --> 05:51.893
- ARE YOU SURE?

05:51.976 --> 05:53.436
- I'M POSITIVE.

05:53.519 --> 05:54.145
THE TERRAIN IS A LITTLE ROUGH,

05:54.228 --> 05:55.271
BUT I'LL GIVE YOU

05:55.354 --> 05:57.482
THE SPEED ADJUSTMENTS
ON THE COURSE.

05:57.565 --> 05:59.108
LIKE WE SAY
IN THE SPACE PROGRAM,

05:59.192 --> 06:01.110
YOU'LL BE GOOD TO GO, BRO.

06:01.194 --> 06:01.944
- IT'S ALL YOU!

06:02.028 --> 06:04.113
- TEAM ROCKET!

06:04.197 --> 06:06.324
- ROCK ON
WITH YOUR BAD SELF.

06:06.783 --> 06:08.701
- YEAH!

06:08.785 --> 06:10.620
[grunts]

06:10.703 --> 06:11.120
WHOA!

06:11.204 --> 06:11.871
[crashing]

06:11.954 --> 06:14.082
all: OOH!

06:14.165 --> 06:15.541
- OW...

06:19.629 --> 06:22.465
[mumbling and moaning]

06:25.009 --> 06:26.761
[thunder crashing]

06:26.844 --> 06:28.596
WHOA-OH!

06:30.306 --> 06:34.393
- COME ON!
YOU CAN DO IT!

06:34.477 --> 06:35.394
- [whimpers]

06:35.478 --> 06:36.687
- WE'VE GOT IT ALL WORKED OUT.

06:36.771 --> 06:39.190
YOU SHOULD GO DOWN THE HILL
INSTEAD OF UP.

06:39.273 --> 06:41.192
[thunder crashing]

06:41.275 --> 06:43.820
- DON'T GO TOO FAST!

06:43.903 --> 06:46.197
- OH-OH!
OH!

06:46.280 --> 06:47.824
[shouting]

06:47.907 --> 06:50.785
WHOA!

06:50.868 --> 06:52.787
[alarm blaring]

06:52.870 --> 06:53.996
AGH!

06:54.080 --> 06:55.164
OH!

06:55.248 --> 06:56.624
OW...

07:00.128 --> 07:01.504
- THERE YOU ARE!
COME ON!

07:01.587 --> 07:03.965
WE'VE GOT TO MEET LARS
ON THE MOUNTAIN IN 15 MINUTES!

07:04.048 --> 07:05.925
- I DON'T CARE.

07:06.008 --> 07:07.385
I CAN'T DO IT.

07:07.468 --> 07:09.637
- BRO, I CAN'T BELIEVE MY EARS.

07:09.720 --> 07:11.055
THIS ISN'T LIKE YOU.

07:11.139 --> 07:12.849
- COME ON, OTTO.
YOU'VE GOT TO DO IT.

07:12.932 --> 07:14.684
- I DON'T GOTTA DO ANYTHING.

07:14.767 --> 07:15.810
- LOOK, YOU SAID IT YOURSELF.

07:15.893 --> 07:18.437
IF LARS WINS,
HE'S GONNA BUST YOU

07:18.521 --> 07:20.857
TILL YOU'RE IN, LIKE,
THE EIGHTH GRADE.

07:22.984 --> 07:24.277
- I KNOW.
I KNOW.

07:24.360 --> 07:24.944
I JUST GOTTA GET PSYCHED.

07:25.027 --> 07:26.863
THAT'S ALL.

07:26.946 --> 07:28.406
- YOU KNOW, ALL THIS WHINING

07:28.489 --> 07:31.033
REMINDS ME OF THE TIME
RAYMUNDO AND ME

07:31.117 --> 07:34.871
WERE OUT SURFING KAENA POINT
ON AN EPIC DAY.

07:34.954 --> 07:36.706
RAYMUNDO AND I
WERE VERY CHOOSY

07:36.789 --> 07:39.917
ABOUT WHICH 50-FOOT WAVE
WE WERE GONNA RIDE.

07:41.460 --> 07:42.503
[both shouting]

07:52.722 --> 07:54.515
- WASN'T IT SCARY?

07:54.599 --> 07:56.601
- IS A COCONUT BROWN?

07:56.684 --> 07:59.770
ESPECIALLY WHEN I LANDED
ON THE POINT OF KAENA POINT.

07:59.854 --> 08:02.023
- OH, MAN!

08:02.106 --> 08:04.984
- PSYCH OUT!
[laughs]

08:05.067 --> 08:06.569
- TITO!

08:06.652 --> 08:08.571
- SORRY, LITTLE CUZ.
HAD TO DO IT.

08:08.654 --> 08:11.449
ACTUALLY,
THIS IS AN APPENDIX SCAR.

08:11.532 --> 08:13.784
- I THINK WHAT TITO'S
TRYING TO SAY, OTTO, IS,

08:13.868 --> 08:15.369
JUST GO FOR IT!

08:15.453 --> 08:16.954
- ALOHA TO THAT.

08:17.038 --> 08:18.289
YOU CAN DO IT, CUZ.

08:18.372 --> 08:20.249
- COME ON.
YOU'RE ROCKET BOY.

08:20.333 --> 08:23.085
- DUH!
OF COURSE HE IS, SAM.

08:26.088 --> 08:28.090
- OKAY.

08:28.174 --> 08:31.260
ANYBODY FOR A LITTLE
MOUNTAIN BOARDING?

08:31.344 --> 08:32.094
- YEAH!
- YAHOO!

08:32.178 --> 08:35.932
- GO, OTTO!

08:36.015 --> 08:37.433
[wind whistling]

08:37.515 --> 08:39.894
- WE'RE WITH YOU, OTTO, MAN.

08:39.977 --> 08:41.645
- COME ON!
YOU CAN DO IT!

08:45.399 --> 08:47.276
- IS THE LITTLE KIDDIE SCARED

08:47.360 --> 08:48.778
ABOUT THE WHOMPING
HE'S GONNA GET

08:48.861 --> 08:50.655
FROM BRUISED MAN'S CURVE?

08:55.910 --> 08:58.788
- OKAY, LARS,
SAY WHATEVER YOU WANT ABOUT ME.

08:58.871 --> 09:00.456
I AM OUT OF HERE.

09:00.539 --> 09:02.208
- HEY, THAT'S NO FUN.
COME ON.

09:02.291 --> 09:03.626
YOU'RE JUST GONNA WALK AWAY?

09:03.709 --> 09:05.795
- WHAT DOES IT LOOK LIKE
I'M DOING?

09:05.878 --> 09:10.091
- [laughs]

09:10.174 --> 09:14.178
OH!
WHOA! WHOA!

09:14.262 --> 09:16.138
- LARS ALERT!

09:16.222 --> 09:16.973
- THIS IS NOT GOOD.

09:17.056 --> 09:19.141
- [screams]

09:19.225 --> 09:21.811
WHOO!
OH-OH-OH!

09:21.894 --> 09:23.187
WHOA!

09:23.271 --> 09:24.480
OH!

09:28.693 --> 09:30.653
OH, OW!
OH!

09:30.736 --> 09:34.156
MY LEG!

09:34.240 --> 09:36.033
MOMMY...

09:37.952 --> 09:39.245
- HA!

09:39.328 --> 09:41.289
I THINK YOU'LL LIVE,
YOU BIG BABY.

09:44.292 --> 09:47.044
[hawk screeching]

09:47.128 --> 09:49.672
- I CAN DO IT.

09:49.755 --> 09:52.174
I AM ROCKET BOY.

09:52.258 --> 09:54.343
HEADS UP, YOU GUYS!

09:54.427 --> 09:56.095
I'M GOOD TO GO!

09:56.178 --> 09:57.096
[all gasping]

09:57.179 --> 09:59.307
- ROCKET BOY!

10:01.309 --> 10:04.270
[lively music]

10:04.353 --> 10:12.361
♪ ♪

10:38.804 --> 10:39.722
- YES!

10:39.805 --> 10:41.390
YES! YEAH!

10:41.474 --> 10:44.518
all: GO, OTTO!
GO, OTTO!

10:44.602 --> 10:46.062
IT'S YOUR BIRTHDAY!
IT'S YOUR BIRTHDAY!

10:46.145 --> 10:48.731
- I DID IT!

10:48.814 --> 10:51.567
I CAN'T BELIEVE
I'M THE FIRST KID

10:51.650 --> 10:53.861
DOWN BRUISED MAN'S CURVE.

10:53.944 --> 10:55.571
- NEITHER CAN I.

10:55.654 --> 10:57.239
ARE YOU SURE THIS SCRATCH
ISN'T INFECTED?

10:57.323 --> 10:59.367
HUH?
[whimpers]

10:59.450 --> 11:01.911
- GET REAL, LARS.

11:04.038 --> 11:05.081
- DAD! DAD! DAD!

11:05.164 --> 11:07.041
- WHAT'S ALL THE COMMOTION?
WHA--

11:07.124 --> 11:11.045
- I TOOK A MOUNTAIN BOARD RUN
DOWN BRUISED MAN'S CURVE!

11:11.128 --> 11:13.255
- NO ONE'S EVER MADE IT DOWN
BEFORE.

11:13.339 --> 11:15.341
- JUST LIKE YOU AND TITO
SURFING 50-FOOT WAVES

11:15.424 --> 11:16.801
AT KAENA POINT!

11:16.884 --> 11:18.511
- TITO SAID WE RODE
50-FOOT WAVES WHERE?

11:18.594 --> 11:21.680
OH, YEAH!
THOSE WAVES...

11:26.060 --> 11:27.937
[together]
WHOA!

11:28.020 --> 11:29.647
- HOW DID YOU KNOW?

11:29.730 --> 11:31.440
- WE WANTED TO HAVE SOMETHING
TO CELEBRATE

11:31.524 --> 11:33.651
WHETHER YOU MADE IT DOWN
IN ONE PIECE OR NOT.

11:33.734 --> 11:36.237
- COOL!
THANKS, YOU GUYS.

11:39.573 --> 11:43.285
- 50-FOOT WAVES
AT KAENA POINT?

11:43.369 --> 11:46.789
- CUZ NEEDED A LITTLE
REALISTIC MOTIVATION, BROTHER.

11:46.872 --> 11:49.458
[laughter]

11:58.384 --> 12:01.971
{\an8}[all cheering]

12:02.054 --> 12:03.556
{\an8}- RIGHT ON, YEAH!

12:03.639 --> 12:04.014
{\an8}- WHOO-HOO!

12:04.098 --> 12:05.850
{\an8}WHOO!

12:09.228 --> 12:11.188
{\an8}HUH?

12:12.940 --> 12:13.274
- UGH!
- AH-OOH!

12:13.357 --> 12:15.985
HEY!

12:16.068 --> 12:17.653
- HEY, WHY DID WE STOP?

12:17.736 --> 12:17.820
- THAT!

12:20.614 --> 12:22.575
- SO SOMEBODY'S GETTING
A NEW POOL.

12:22.658 --> 12:23.534
BIG DEAL.

12:23.617 --> 12:25.369
- NOT JUST SOMEBODY...
- WHOA!

12:25.453 --> 12:27.121
- OUR NEW BEST BUD,

12:27.204 --> 12:29.290
EDDIE, PRINCE
OF THE NETHERWORLD.

12:29.373 --> 12:32.960
- HEY, I COULD USE A COOL,
REFRESHING DIP RIGHT NOW.

12:33.043 --> 12:34.587
- BUT IT'S EDDIE'S POOL.

12:34.670 --> 12:38.340
MAYBE HE FILLS IT
WITH GROSS NETHERWORLD STUFF.

12:38.424 --> 12:40.468
- TWIST, HE JUST DRESSES WEIRD.

12:40.551 --> 12:42.970
I'M SURE HIS POOL IS FINE.
COME ON.

12:43.053 --> 12:43.721
LET'S CHECK IT OUT.

12:43.804 --> 12:46.265
- NOT SO FAST, ROCKET BOY.

12:46.348 --> 12:48.642
WE GOT TO HELP DAD IN THE SHOP,
REMEMBER?

12:48.726 --> 12:51.187
- I CAN'T HEAR YOU!

12:57.943 --> 12:58.694
[together]
WHOA!

12:58.777 --> 13:01.864
[inspirational harp flourish]

13:01.947 --> 13:04.867
- EMPTY POOL
EQUALS SKATEBOARD PARADISE!

13:04.950 --> 13:07.870
- TONIGHT,
BY THE GREAT MOON'S LIGHT,

13:07.953 --> 13:09.705
WE SHALL FILL IT
AND GIVE IT LIFE!

13:09.788 --> 13:11.415
LIFE!
LIFE, I SAY!

13:11.499 --> 13:12.875
[laughs]

13:12.958 --> 13:15.544
MY DAD SAYS THAT WE'RE GONNA
HAVE A POOL PARTY REAL SOON.

13:15.628 --> 13:18.047
- FILLING IT UP TONIGHT?

13:18.130 --> 13:20.508
THIS IS, LIKE, THE MOST PERFECT
EMPTY POOL I'VE EVER SEEN.

13:20.591 --> 13:23.552
YOU GOTTA LET US SKATE IT FIRST.

13:23.636 --> 13:25.429
- THE KING OF THE NETHERWORLD
AND HIS BETROTHED

13:25.513 --> 13:28.933
HAVE BANISHED ALL TRAVELERS

13:29.016 --> 13:31.894
WHILE THEY ARE ABROAD
FROM THIS KINGDOM.

13:31.977 --> 13:33.312
- HUH?

13:33.395 --> 13:34.396
- I'M NOT ALLOWED
TO HAVE FRIENDS OVER

13:34.480 --> 13:36.899
WHILE MY MOM AND DAD
AREN'T HOME.

13:36.982 --> 13:37.942
- COME ON.

13:38.025 --> 13:39.735
THERE'LL NEVER BE
ANOTHER CHANCE.

13:39.818 --> 13:42.071
I'LL TEACH YOU
SOME NEW TRICKS.

13:42.154 --> 13:46.200
- OKAY, BUT ONLY IF YOU PROMISE
TO KEEP THIS A SECRET.

13:46.283 --> 13:48.327
IF THE KING OF THE NETHERWORLD
FINDS OUT,

13:48.410 --> 13:50.454
I'M TOAST.

13:50.538 --> 13:53.040
- EDDIE, YOU RULE...

13:53.123 --> 13:53.415
THE NETHERWORLD.

13:53.499 --> 13:55.376
- I DO?

13:55.459 --> 13:56.377
both: WOOGIE-WOOGITY-WOOGITY,
WOOGITY!

13:56.460 --> 13:59.129
- OTTO, HELLO?

13:59.213 --> 14:01.006
ME AND YOU HELP RAYMUNDO?

14:01.090 --> 14:02.258
WE'RE GONNA BE LATE.

14:02.341 --> 14:03.759
- REG, CAN'T YOU JUST GO

14:03.842 --> 14:06.303
AND TELL HIM WE'LL DEFINITELY
DO IT TONIGHT?

14:06.387 --> 14:08.180
- NO, OTTO.
I CAN'T.

14:08.264 --> 14:09.598
WE PROMISED.

14:09.682 --> 14:11.517
- WHY DON'T WE DO
WHAT MY MOM ALWAYS SAYS TO DO?

14:11.600 --> 14:13.602
- I <i> AM</i> WEARING CLEAN UNDERWEAR.

14:13.686 --> 14:14.603
- NO!

14:14.687 --> 14:15.854
GET YOUR WORK DONE,

14:15.938 --> 14:18.607
AND THEN COME BACK HERE
AND TEAR THIS POOL UP LATER.

14:18.691 --> 14:20.192
- RIGHT ON, SAMMY.

14:20.276 --> 14:21.485
THAT WAY, DAD ISN'T MAD,

14:21.569 --> 14:23.571
AND WE CAN HAVE
THE WHOLE AFTERNOON TO SKATE.

14:23.654 --> 14:25.614
- [groans]
ALL RIGHT.

14:25.698 --> 14:26.991
THANKS, EDDIE!

14:27.074 --> 14:28.200
CATCH YOU IN A FEW.

14:28.284 --> 14:29.410
YOU'RE THE GREATEST.

14:29.493 --> 14:30.452
[together]
LATER!

14:30.536 --> 14:32.413
- DON'T FORGET!

14:32.496 --> 14:33.956
IT'S OUR SECRET!

14:37.376 --> 14:39.962
- OUT OF MY WAY!

14:40.045 --> 14:43.799
I DON'T WANT TO MISS A MINUTE
OF EDDIE'S EMPTY POOL ACTION.

14:43.882 --> 14:44.967
- OTTO, SHH!

14:45.050 --> 14:46.343
YOU PROMISED EDDIE
YOU WOULDN'T--

14:46.427 --> 14:48.470
- LATER!
MUCH!

14:49.972 --> 14:50.848
[whooshing]

14:50.931 --> 14:51.473
[seagull screeches]

14:51.557 --> 14:53.350
YEAH-AH!
WHOO!

14:53.434 --> 14:56.687
[laughs]

14:56.770 --> 14:58.272
HEADS UP!

14:58.355 --> 15:00.733
- HEY!
WHAT THE--

15:00.816 --> 15:02.067
- HUH?

15:03.360 --> 15:06.989
YAHOO!

15:07.072 --> 15:08.824
- OH!
- [shrieks]

15:08.907 --> 15:11.869
- WHAT IS YOUR PROBLEM, OTTO?

15:11.952 --> 15:14.496
- YEAH, LOOK WHERE
YOU'RE SHREDDING.

15:14.580 --> 15:16.415
- SORRY.
DON'T HAVE TIME TO TALK.

15:16.498 --> 15:19.209
EDDIE'S GOT A NEW POOL,
AND IT'S TOTALLY EMPTY.

15:19.293 --> 15:21.670
I'M HEADING OVER
FOR SOME INSANE POOL ACTION

15:21.754 --> 15:24.590
AS SOON AS I FINISH HELPING
RAYMUNDO.

15:24.673 --> 15:25.716
- POOL?

15:25.799 --> 15:27.760
- THAT SOUNDS SO COOL!

15:27.843 --> 15:29.345
- IT IS COOL!

15:29.428 --> 15:30.721
LATER!

15:30.804 --> 15:32.890
- THANKS FOR THE INVITE!

15:34.141 --> 15:38.270
- HE DIDN'T JUST DO
WHAT I THINK HE DID...

15:40.939 --> 15:41.774
- HEY, TROUPERS!

15:41.857 --> 15:42.483
HOW'S IT GOING DOWN HERE?

15:42.566 --> 15:44.276
- GREAT.
- FINE.

15:44.360 --> 15:44.902
- COOL.

15:44.985 --> 15:45.527
- ARE WE DONE YET?

15:45.611 --> 15:47.696
- UH, NO.

15:47.780 --> 15:49.198
I REALLY APPRECIATE YOU GUYS
HELPING OUT

15:49.281 --> 15:50.866
WHILE WE'RE SWAMPED UPSTAIRS.

15:50.949 --> 15:52.034
- NO PROBLEMO.

15:52.117 --> 15:52.743
- THAT'S MY GANG!

15:52.826 --> 15:55.120
NOW GET BACK TO WORK.

15:56.705 --> 15:59.833
- MAN, I'M NEVER GONNA MAKE IT
TO EDDIE'S.

15:59.917 --> 16:02.836
- I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU BLABBED
TO TRISH AND SHERRY

16:02.920 --> 16:03.754
AFTER YOU PROMISED EDDIE.

16:03.837 --> 16:07.383
- WHAT?
NO BIGGIE. RELAX.

16:07.466 --> 16:09.009
- HELLO, YOUNG ROCKET CREW.

16:09.093 --> 16:10.469
WHAT'S THE 411?

16:10.552 --> 16:13.055
HEY, IT'S NOT LIKE YOU
TO MISS A SATURDAY AT MADTOWN.

16:13.138 --> 16:16.016
EH, RAYMUNDO GOT YOU
WORKING HARD, EH?

16:16.100 --> 16:17.726
- WE HAVE TO HELP DAD OUT
FOR A LITTLE WHILE

16:17.810 --> 16:19.353
THIS AFTERNOON, CONROY.

16:19.436 --> 16:21.939
- AND THEN WE'RE GONNA DO
SOME INSANE BOWL RIDING

16:22.022 --> 16:22.690
OVER AT EDDIE'S HOUSE!

16:22.773 --> 16:23.899
[together]
OTTO!

16:23.982 --> 16:26.652
- EDDIE,
PRINCE OF WHATEVERS-WORLD,

16:26.735 --> 16:28.821
GOT A SKATEPARK AT HIS HOUSE?

16:28.904 --> 16:31.281
- NO, HE'S GOT
A BRAND-NEW EMPTY POOL

16:31.365 --> 16:32.908
THAT HIS PARENTS JUST BUILT,

16:32.991 --> 16:34.827
AND HE SAID I COULD TEAR IT UP!

16:34.910 --> 16:36.120
- REALLY?

16:37.162 --> 16:39.123
- DID YOU AND TWISTER
TRADE BRAINS?

16:39.206 --> 16:42.418
YOU JUST TOLD CONROY
ABOUT THE EMPTY POOL.

16:42.501 --> 16:44.962
- YOU PROMISED EDDIE
YOU WOULDN'T SAY ANYTHING.

16:45.045 --> 16:47.840
- CHILL OUT.
LIKE EDDIE REALLY CARES.

16:47.923 --> 16:49.258
[feedback screeching]

16:49.341 --> 16:51.176
- ATTENTION, MADTOWN SKATERS.

16:51.260 --> 16:53.595
AS A SPECIAL TREAT,
WORD IS THAT

16:53.679 --> 16:55.556
THERE IS SOME INSANE
SKATING SESSION

16:55.639 --> 16:56.640
TAKING PLACE THIS AFTERNOON

16:56.724 --> 16:59.768
AT EDDIE, PRINCE OF THE--
THE NETHER--

16:59.852 --> 17:01.311
AT EDDIE'S HOUSE,

17:01.395 --> 17:03.564
WHERE THERE IS
A BRAND-NEW EMPTY POOL.

17:03.647 --> 17:04.897
BRING YOUR GUTS

17:04.982 --> 17:07.859
FOR THIS ONCE-IN-A-LIFETIME
CHANCE!

17:07.943 --> 17:09.611
THAT IS ALL.

17:09.694 --> 17:12.740
- [grunting]

17:14.074 --> 17:16.868
- WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
I WHOMPED YOU?

17:16.952 --> 17:18.244
- THIS MORNING.

17:18.328 --> 17:19.913
- YOU'RE OVERDUE.

17:19.997 --> 17:21.165
- [wails]

17:21.248 --> 17:21.832
[laughter]

17:21.915 --> 17:24.041
- OKAY, COUGH IT UP.

17:24.126 --> 17:25.836
WHERE ARE TRISH AND SHERRY
GOING

17:25.919 --> 17:26.587
FOR SOME EMPTY POOL
SKATEBOARDING ACTION

17:26.670 --> 17:28.672
THIS AFTERNOON?

17:28.756 --> 17:30.466
- SKATEBOARDING?

17:30.549 --> 17:32.301
WHAT COULD YOU POSSIBLY MEAN?

17:32.384 --> 17:33.051
- CAN IT, SQUIRT!

17:33.135 --> 17:35.262
IF YOU DON'T TELL US,

17:35.345 --> 17:36.096
I'LL JUST WHOMP IT
OUT OF YOU.

17:36.180 --> 17:39.892
- ASK OTTO!
ASK OTTO!

17:39.975 --> 17:40.058
[groans]

17:43.687 --> 17:44.646
OH, MAN.

17:44.730 --> 17:47.107
- [growls]

17:47.191 --> 17:48.525
AREN'T WE DONE YET?

17:48.609 --> 17:50.235
I WANT TO SKATE!

17:50.319 --> 17:53.697
- WE ARE NOT DONE UNPACKING
THESE BOXES OF SHOES, OTTO.

17:53.781 --> 17:55.407
- I'M SICK OF THIS WORK.

17:55.491 --> 17:58.160
I WANT TO SKATE
EDDIE'S EMPTY POOL NOW!

17:58.243 --> 17:58.660
- AHA!

17:58.744 --> 18:00.662
[all shout]

18:00.746 --> 18:02.122
EDDIE,
PRINCE OF THE DARK WORLD,

18:02.206 --> 18:05.459
HAS GOT AN EMPTY POOL, HUH?

18:05.542 --> 18:07.503
- THIS IS GONNA BE
TOTALLY SWEET!

18:07.586 --> 18:09.963
[laughter]

18:12.591 --> 18:15.761
- HOW MANY PEOPLE
ARE YOU GOING TO TELL?

18:15.844 --> 18:17.429
- IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

18:17.513 --> 18:19.097
ME AND TWISTER
CAN HANDLE THEM.

18:19.181 --> 18:20.265
- WE CAN?

18:20.349 --> 18:22.184
- WHAT CAN YOU HANDLE?

18:24.645 --> 18:26.063
WHAT IS GOING ON?

18:26.146 --> 18:28.273
- PLEASE, DAD, PLEASE.

18:28.357 --> 18:29.817
EDDIE, PRINCE
OF THE NETHERWORLD,

18:29.900 --> 18:31.485
HAS GOT A BRAND-SPANKING-NEW
EMPTY POOL,

18:31.568 --> 18:33.529
AND WE CAN BE THE FIRST ONES
TO TEAR IT UP.

18:33.612 --> 18:35.697
- [sighs]

18:35.781 --> 18:37.699
OKAY, GO AHEAD.
SCRAM.

18:37.783 --> 18:38.867
HAVE A GREAT TIME!

18:38.951 --> 18:41.912
[together]
YEAH!

18:41.995 --> 18:43.288
- [sighs]

18:43.372 --> 18:45.582
RAYMUNDO, YOU ARE SO COOL.

18:45.666 --> 18:47.751
[laughs]

18:47.835 --> 18:49.837
[grunts]

18:57.177 --> 18:58.053
- COME ON, REG!

18:58.136 --> 19:00.305
FOLLOW THE LEADER!

19:00.389 --> 19:01.640
WHOA!
YEAH!

19:01.723 --> 19:03.016
YEAH!

19:03.100 --> 19:04.726
- [grunting]

19:08.063 --> 19:09.731
- YEAH!

19:09.815 --> 19:11.441
- WHOO-HOO!

19:17.322 --> 19:19.449
- COME ON, SAM!
- GO, SAMMY!

19:19.533 --> 19:21.076
- [sighs]

19:21.159 --> 19:22.119
OH! OH!

19:22.202 --> 19:23.787
OH!

19:28.125 --> 19:30.586
COME ON, EDDIE.
YOU'RE UP.

19:30.669 --> 19:31.712
- I DON'T THINK
THE PRINCE OF THE NETHERWORLD

19:31.795 --> 19:34.298
NEEDS ANY MORE SCABS.

19:34.381 --> 19:36.341
all: EDDIE, COME ON!

19:36.425 --> 19:37.593
[phone ringing]

19:37.676 --> 19:40.387
- MY MOM!

19:43.515 --> 19:44.224
BUT I--NO, I WASN'T--

19:44.308 --> 19:46.518
OF COURSE NO ONE IS HERE.

19:46.602 --> 19:49.438
- YAHOO!

19:49.521 --> 19:51.523
- UH, THAT'S THE TV.

19:51.607 --> 19:53.275
MOM!

19:53.358 --> 19:55.027
THE POOL IS EMPTY.

19:55.110 --> 19:57.905
WHAT WOULD I BE DOING
HAVING A PARTY?

19:57.988 --> 19:59.406
YES, MA'AM.

20:03.619 --> 20:06.246
[screams]

20:06.330 --> 20:07.664
- YEAH!
- OW!

20:07.748 --> 20:10.626
- YEAH!
AW!

20:10.709 --> 20:12.002
OOH, BIG AIR!
YEAH!

20:12.085 --> 20:13.420
- I AM SUCH TOAST.

20:13.503 --> 20:16.882
- YOU'RE GONNA GET EDDIE
IN ALL SORTS OF TROUBLE.

20:16.965 --> 20:18.258
- LIKE I CARE ABOUT THAT FREAK.

20:18.342 --> 20:22.471
- WHAT PLAGUE HAVE YOU VISITED
UPON MY HOUSE?

20:22.554 --> 20:24.973
OTTO, YOU PROMISED
TO KEEP THIS SECRET.

20:25.057 --> 20:27.517
- NICE GOING, BIG MOUTH.

20:27.601 --> 20:28.727
- I CAN HANDLE IT.

20:28.810 --> 20:29.937
- NO, YOU CAN'T!

20:30.020 --> 20:31.647
WAH!
HA!

20:31.730 --> 20:35.108
- IT WAS SUCH A MISTAKE
TO TELL YOU GUYS.

20:35.192 --> 20:37.903
- TWISTER, HELP ME OUT HERE.

20:37.986 --> 20:39.321
- WHAT DO YOU WANT ME
TO DO?

20:39.404 --> 20:40.656
I ALREADY GOT TWO WHOMPINGS,

20:40.739 --> 20:42.741
AND I'M PROBABLY OVERDUE
FOR MY THIRD.

20:42.824 --> 20:44.076
- WHOO!
- [laughs]

20:44.159 --> 20:45.702
- LOOK, EDDIE, I'M SORRY.

20:45.786 --> 20:47.245
EVERYTHING'S UNDER CONTROL.

20:47.329 --> 20:49.331
LARS WILL BE OUT OF HERE
IN NO TIME.

20:49.414 --> 20:50.624
- HEY, EDDIE!

20:50.707 --> 20:52.167
OTTO TOLD US YOU WERE HAVING

20:52.250 --> 20:55.087
A PRE-FILL POOL PARTY
FOR THE SKATERS IN TOWN.

20:55.170 --> 20:57.673
NICE!

20:57.756 --> 20:58.882
- [shouts]

20:58.966 --> 21:00.592
BETRAYER!

21:00.676 --> 21:03.178
[sobbing]

21:03.261 --> 21:05.180
- I, UH...
OKAY, OKAY.

21:05.263 --> 21:07.432
IT'S NOT GONNA GET ANY WORSE,
I SWEAR.

21:07.516 --> 21:08.892
- HEY, ISN'T IT SO COOL
THAT EDDIE--

21:08.976 --> 21:10.936
- EVERYONE WILL GET A TURN.

21:11.019 --> 21:14.064
PLEASE STAY IN YOUR LINES!

21:14.147 --> 21:16.525
OTTO, LOOK WHAT YOU DID!

21:16.608 --> 21:17.609
EDDIE IS SO BUSTED!

21:17.693 --> 21:20.195
- I GUESS I WAS SO EXCITED
ABOUT THE POOL,

21:20.278 --> 21:22.114
I KIND OF BRAGGED ABOUT IT
A LITTLE.

21:22.197 --> 21:23.407
- A LITTLE?

21:23.490 --> 21:25.409
I HAVE SOMETHING
YOU CAN BRAG ABOUT--

21:25.492 --> 21:27.369
HOW YOU GOT EVERYBODY
OUT OF HERE

21:27.452 --> 21:28.620
AND THE PLACE CLEANED UP

21:28.704 --> 21:29.579
BEFORE EDDIE'S PARENTS
GOT HOME.

21:29.663 --> 21:31.915
NOW!

21:31.999 --> 21:33.500
- GOT IT.

21:33.583 --> 21:35.002
TWIST, WE NEED A PLAN.

21:35.085 --> 21:37.963
- HMM, WE COULD TELL THEM

21:38.046 --> 21:39.881
AN ALIEN INVASION IS HAPPENING.

21:39.965 --> 21:41.258
- [groans]

21:41.341 --> 21:43.343
SAM, PLEASE HELP.

21:43.427 --> 21:44.720
- HMM...

21:44.803 --> 21:45.887
I THINK I GOT IT.

21:45.971 --> 21:47.597
LEAVE IT TO ME.

21:47.681 --> 21:49.850
ATTENTION, SKATERS.

21:49.933 --> 21:53.020
ATTENTION,
SKATERS.

21:53.103 --> 21:55.897
[whistles]

21:55.981 --> 21:57.149
[tires screech]

21:57.232 --> 21:59.568
FREE ICE CREAM
AND FRENCH FRIES

21:59.651 --> 22:02.404
FOR EVERYONE
AT THE SHORE SHACK!

22:02.487 --> 22:03.780
GO GET IT!

22:03.864 --> 22:06.908
[all cheering]

22:12.372 --> 22:13.790
IT WORKED.

22:13.874 --> 22:16.626
JUST CALL ME
SAM THE SUPER GENIUS.

22:16.710 --> 22:19.337
- ONLY ONE PROBLEM,
SUPER GENIUS.

22:19.421 --> 22:20.797
- WHAT'S THAT?

22:20.881 --> 22:23.383
- WHO'S GONNA PAY FOR
ALL THE FRIES AND ICE CREAM?

22:23.467 --> 22:24.342
- OOPS!

22:24.426 --> 22:26.470
[all screaming]

22:29.723 --> 22:32.976
- PHEW!

22:33.060 --> 22:34.895
[giggles]

22:34.978 --> 22:38.315
- EDDIE, SWEETIE,
WE CAME HOME EARLY!

22:41.276 --> 22:43.361
[kids laughing and shouting]

22:45.280 --> 22:48.700
- UH, DAD, WOULD YOU MIND

22:48.784 --> 22:51.411
IF WE HAD A FEW FRIENDS OVER
FOR LUNCH?

23:38.458 --> 23:40.168
{\an8}- OTTO SAYS, "LET'S ROCK!"
